Class DREException

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class DREException
extends InternationalizedException

This is the superclass for all exceptions in DRE.

DREException extends InternationalizedException for internationalization support. Since DRE Exceptions are internationalized, the thrower does not supply a hard coded message. Instead, the thrower specifies a key that identifies the message. That key is then looked up in a locale-specific ResourceBundle to find the actual message associated with this exception.

The thrower may specify the name of the ResourceBundle in which to find the exception message. Any name may be used. If the name is omitted, the resource bundle identified by STANDARD_MESSAGE_CATALOG will be used. This contains the standard DRE exception messages.

Author:
Santthosh Babu Selvadurai
